WEBVTT

00:10:58.544 --> 00:11:02.110
We reminded them that when
workers have more money,

00:11:02.110 --> 00:11:03.822
businesses have more customers,

00:11:03.822 --> 00:11:05.804
and need more employees.

00:11:05.804 --> 00:11:08.490
We reminded them that when businesses

00:11:08.490 --> 00:11:11.210
pay workers a living wage,

00:11:11.210 --> 00:11:13.102
taxpayers are relieved of the burden

00:11:13.102 --> 00:11:14.812
of funding the poverty programs

00:11:14.812 --> 00:11:17.714
like food stamps and medical assistance

00:11:17.714 --> 00:11:19.424
and rent assistance

00:11:19.424 --> 00:11:21.820
that those workers need.

00:11:21.820 --> 00:11:24.784
We reminded them that low-wage workers

00:11:24.784 --> 00:11:27.110
make terrible taxpayers,

00:11:27.110 --> 00:11:29.128
and that when you raise the minimum wage

00:11:29.128 --> 00:11:31.253
for all businesses,